Text.string: Good show, Vault Hunter! You certainly gave those bandits a walloping!

Jakobs loyalists are comin' outta the woodwork, thanks to you and Clay. We might just take back this planet yet. Meanwhile, I got that record player workin'. Swing by the lodge, and let's have a listen.
Pa... I'll never forget your last words—
Oh, wait, wait, wait, wait—I'm pickin' up an ECHO signal. Hell yeah, I'm saved! Over here!
What is going on? Are we under attack?!
Abandon the ship! Robots and children first!
Vault Hunter, I think I have a good use for that combat AI. Bring her to me.
Shut up, bitch! You shoved me in a teddy bear!
Damnation! Ugh, this gut rot's chewing through me like a pig through a pile of apples.
Ah-hah! I know just the one.

All right, that's enough. Now, the Family Jewel is my father's ship. It crashed out in the jungle, not too long after his death. Go find the Jewel, Vault Hunter. If my father's cryptic message is anything to go by, there ought to be a Key fragment on board. Meanwhile, Alistair and I will investigate the other two clues.
All right, BALEX. Where are you?
BALEX? Where are you?
BALEX. Are you nearby?
Computy-man! I'm here, where are ya?
Almost there. But I'm kinda in the middle of somethin'. And that somethin' is a big fuckin' dinosaur! Heads up!
Yeah. I had to make an emergency landing after a... disagreement between me and my combat pilot, GenIVIV.
So, a mutiny?
So you got mutinied?
A mutiny, then.
Ahh, a good ol'-fashioned mutiny, eh?
Sounds better than a messy breakup, so we'll just leave it at that. The emergency hatch over there is held shut with hydraulic lines. Cut those and we're in.
Oh, man, I'm OUT, man! Damn, it was nasty as hell in there. It stunk.
Hey, I don't—I don't wanna talk about it. Why are you lookin' for the Family Jewel?
I can do more than navigate! Vault Hunter, go through the medical bay!
Just a side effect of your loose navigating, BALEX. You took us to a scummy port and didn't get checked! You gave me ratch!
Medical staff only. Clearance required.
Kill it! Come on, man! You gotta kill it!
Man, I HAVE clearance! I'm the navigator!
ERROR: Entity “BALEX” classified as “an unlovable idiot who never satisfied anyone”.
Yeah, I've heard that before! This is GenIVIV's doing. I think I know a way around it, though. Vault Hunter, knock this fool's head off.
Hell yeah. Now install me on the bot!
Oh, man. Oh, it feels so good to move around.
Navigated, bitches! This way, Vault Hunter! We gotta get to the security hold to find that Key fragment.
That's what I'm talkin' about, Vault Hunter! You're a natural bot killer! So... we ain't getting through that door, but I know a side route. Let's go through the freight entrance.
Over here! In the ratty-ass stuffed plushie. Come pick me up!
C'mon, man! I can feel this swamp juice getting in my stuffing!
Navigated, bitches! Follow me!
Watch out—this area ain't safe.
Hell yeah! We crushed those fools!
The Key fragment should be in this security cell! Watch my ass while I “navigate” the door controls.
I've had a lot of free time since you crashed us here, BALEX. Did you know the local jabbers have a unique language just for mating? They're quite the romantics.
I get it! I'm no good at dirty talk! Shut up about it.
You want to hear some? It's really beautiful.
Why are you a plush toy?
Ohhohhh, aren't you just delightful. Mhh.
Is this your... default physical state?
Oh-hohoho, that is cute!
Ooh, ooh, aaah! Eee-eee! Wagh! Agh, ooh, hoo!
Ah, crap! She's calling all the horny jabbers back to us! I hate them things!
[mild jabber sex noises]
[mild jabber sex noises]
[mild jabber sex noises]
[mild jabber sex noises]
[mild jabber sex noises]
I turned on some turrets! Get back, you horny weirdos!
I'm getting some turrets online!
I'm trying to block the hole but they just keep coming!
That's what the jabbers said! Hahahahaha!
Shut up, GenIVIV!
That was... really uncomfortable. Come back, I've nearly got the cell open.
Tadaaaaaaaa||aaaaaaaaa||aaaaaaaaa!
While you freed Reliance from the grip of those COV devils, I got that damn record contraption working. Let's find out where the Vault Key's hidden. Will you do the honors, Vault Hunter?
Ah, a trek deep into untamed lands! I am envious, Vault Hunter!
Ah, crap.
I moved the Key fragment ages ago, you cutie dummies. If you really want it that bad, you'll have to come to the bridge and fight me for it.
Oh, GENIVIV! My body! My beautiful body! Oh, I hate you.

Okay, listen. I got an idea on how to beat GenIVIV. Now, she's installed herself into a Maliwan mech, but there's a second one in the shuttle bay. If we get me into that one, GenIVIV won't be able to stop us! Let's head through Engineering.
S'up, you chode-toads. Havin' fun slummin' it in “paradise”?
So what now, BALEX?
All right, BALEX, what now?
We've arrived. What is next?
Okay! What's next, then?
Mech time, baby! We gotta open it up and get me inside that beautiful thing.
There's a manual override on top! Just gotta get to it.
Navigated, bitches! Get me inside that mech!
Nice, some ratch! I can finally kick some ass!
Let us know when you've got that Vault open, will ya? It was super nice to have my dinner waiting for me last time, ya know?
Ow!
Damn. Thing's tall as hell. You probably can't reach the head. Uh, just put me wherever I fit.
I'm in! Ha ha, I'm alive!
I'm in! How do I look?
Like Iron Bear at a warehouse rave.
A little... dangly.
I am trying not to look at your plush codpiece. And failing.
So you're just going to... free-bear it?
Okay, yeah, yeah, yeah. I get it, I look a little weird, but, check out these weapons systems!
Later, grundle-humpers!
What? No-no-no-no-no-no-no! Ah, SHIIIIT!
You okay?
So, are you coming back, or...
I assume that was not part of the plan?
So, uh... what now, computy man?
Yeah... why don't you head over to the bridge, the door should be open. I'll... try to stop careening through the air. So, we both have things to do. Teamwork.
I'm at the bridge. BALEX, you here?||Guess not.
BALEX? I'm at the bridge. Hello?||Damn it.
BALEX, I am at the bridge. Do you copy? Be silent once for yes and twice for no.
I'm at the bridge. You copy, computy-man?||Hellooooo?||—Right bastard this guy is.
Oh! Vault Hunter. Not surprised BALEX didn't make it with you. Come on in.
Vault Hunter, I'm almost there! Just gotta solve one problem.
You're not designed to solve problems, BALEX. That's my job. You're just my chauffeur.
Well, what I'm solving is the anti-collision safeguards. Which I just turned off! NAVIGATED, BITCHES!
That's the Jewel? Looks like crap.
The Jewel has seen better days.
The Jewel appears to be in disrepair.
That's the Family Jewel? What the hell happened?
This sucks! Pick me up!
Pick me up, come on!
I don't wanna die in a swamp!
Pick me up!
Ah, crap! That's not how it works in the ECHO shows!
Error. Errorrrr.
I have arms now! Ha ha! What's this do?
Ah, crap! Kill it! KILL IT!
All right! Here, I'll get the door.
Let me see if I can navigate a way around.
Through here!
[medium jabber sex noises]
[medium jabber sex noises]
[medium jabber sex noises]
[medium jabber sex noises]
[medium jabber sex noises]
[intense jabber sex noises]
[intense jabber sex noises]
[intense jabber sex noises]
[intense jabber sex noises]
[intense jabber sex noises]
Done! Navigated, bitches!
Come pick me up!
Man, that felt great. Now, how do I get these hover jets on...
Classic BALEX. Always happy to fly off and try something new, but as soon as there's a problem he just falls apart.
Aw, man! My mech! Finish her off, Vault Hunter!
Now that I got you, takin' back the Jewel's not gonna be no problem. GenIVIV's locked it down tight, but I know all the back routes. Pays to have a navigator on your side, huh?
The hydraulic panel's right next to the hatch. You should be able to reach it.
Yeah, these sticky bitches get stuck all the time. Just smack it.
Aw, crap. The ratches are back. I thought I got that cleared up. Cut those hydraulic lines!
To think, these might be the last words of Montgomery Jakobs.
That's it! The hatch is open. That Vault Key fragment is ours!
BALEX, you little cutie idiot! Why are you here? Didn't I install you in a kid's toy and toss you out with the trash?
Ugggh, they get it, Troy.
Cram it, GenIVIV! I got a friend now! We're here for the Key fragment. I know you got it in the security hold!
Oh, sorry. That's spoken for. Aurelia said if I brought it back to her, she'd buy me a dreadnaught. So I'm gonna do that!
There's a piece of a Vault Key in it. Wainwright Jakobs sent me.
Wainwright Jakobs said there would be a Vault Key fragment in the ship.
I hunt a Vault Key fragment, and Wainwright Jakobs tells me there is one on the ship.
This youngster named Wainwright says there's a piece of a Vault Key onboard.
Ah, crap, I navigated again. Stupid!
Oh, not opening this one for you. Now, I'm just a heartless combat AI, but are locked doors harder to navigate?
She's screwin' with my route! That's messed up!
Passenger has touched the hot wires. Dispensing care to the big baby who can't function around modern technology.
I'm DRUNK!
Oh, see? It worked out! Nothing to worry about. No reason to be mad at me.
“Big baby” all cleaned up. Dispensing lollipop... Error. No treats found.
Oh, you're with Wainwright? Okay, all right. Yeah, yeah, I'll show you where the Family Jewel is. It's in a gorge nearby. I can get you inside.
Oh, BALEX! Guess what I just found on the bridge? Montgomery Jakobs' collection of antique maps! How about that?
I don't care! Why would I care about some precious irreplaceable maps? Come on, stop it. That's dumb.
Oh, yeah. Totally. Who cares?||[ripping noise]
That better not be the last known astrograph of the Talos Empire!
Oh, you know what? I think it's that one that you said.
ARGGGH! GenIVIV!
“BALEX”. What kind of a name is that?
“BALEX”... is that short for something?
“BALEX”. Your designation intrigues me.
So's “BALEX” yer first name, or...
Oh dear.

Oh yeah, yeah, yeah. It stands for Binary Automated Logistical...||All right, my old man Jakobs couldn't decide whether to call me Barry or Alex so he ended up calling me BALEX. I know it's not the coolest origin story.
Nah, I get it. I'm Moserah Hayussinian Yan-Lun al-Amir Andreyevna. Call me Moze.
I'm Amara. It means “deathless” on thirty-seven worlds, and it's a brand of conditioner on eight.
My 512-character alphanumeric designation has no meaning, but I have shortened it to “FL4K” for the sake of time.
Hey, could've been worse. My brothers were named Baron and Captain. I got off lucky with Zane!
Damn. Well, we all got off better than “GenIVIV”. That ain't even how numerals work.
Vault Hunter, I'm sorry you have to see what's turning out to be a very messy breakup. I really thought BALEX and I were made for each other. He took me places, and I killed people there!
It was never gonna work, GenIVIV! We're from two different manufacturers! That, and you betrayed the Jakobs family. But MOSTLY the manufacturer thing.
We're coming up on the security hold. It'll be right around... ah crap, I'm navigating again. You know what? You find it.
Ah, crap. More bots.
Not if we get it first! We're comin' for that fragment!
Uh huh, come on in. Whatcha gonna do, navigate me to death? Chart a course up your own ass. Phbbbbt.
There's the door to the security hold! And GenIVIV's barricaded it. My medbot clearance won't do anything here. Great!
Ah, this sucks! Help! Help!
Oh, security! There's an adorable little idiot criminal trying to break in. Please pull him apart. Slowly.
I'm NOT adorable. Ah, crap, here they come!
You have acquired the first fragment of Eden-6's Vault Key. Bring it to me aboard Sanctuary.
I am in my lab with Lilith. We are storming our brains on ways to combat the Calypsos. Bring the fragment to me.
Gahahahaha, ahahahaha!
What the hell? Vault Hunter, we're locked in here. Get to the bridge and fix this.
Hahaha! Idiots!
A little help here? Don't step on the chip.
Aw, nah, I know that evil laugh anywhere. GenIVIV is all up in your ship!
Hey, cutie idiots! I like your ship. Not as well-armed as the Family Jewel, but I think I'll fit right in here once I make some modifications. Oh, on-board service bots? Please take apart the crew.
Slow down, whoever you are. I'm looking for the Family Jewel.
Hello! Maybe you can help me? I'm looking for the Family Jewel?
Who are you? And do you know where I can find the Family Jewel?
Who's blabberin' while I commune with nature and shite? Unless you know where the Family Jewel is, shut your face!

I'm going to fly you, the Key fragment, and your whole ship to Aurelia! And once she rewards me with a dreadnaught, I'll travel from system to system, burning every inhabited planet I find!||I've always wanted to take a vacation.
Vault Hunter! She's got her claws in your computer system. You can't hurt her from here. I gotta go in myself. Plug me in!
All right, GenIVIV. Get the hell out!
Make me!
Rgggh, agh, rrgh!
Noooo!
Hah! I shoved her ass in a hard drive and ejected the bitch! Pick her up, Vault Hunter!
Damn, this place is lookin' nasty.
All right, now go put her in something where she can't screw up anything, like a toilet, or... or a broken toilet!
Screw you! I'll kill you all!
Oh, I know the Family Jewel. I'm BALEX, the ship's navigator! I'll prove it. Here's coordinates for my ass, now come save it!
Hah-hah! Sucks to suck, GenIVIV! Okay, everyone, I'm turning off the lockdown and getting your ship back to normal.
Now that we are past that nonsense, bring the Key fragment to me.
Thank you. Our incarceration was not without fruit. We may have a plan to open the Vault without giving the Calypsos what they want again.
Now that we know they're after the power of the Vault monster itself, we can hurt them. Tannis is looking into a way for you to destroy the monster before Tyreen can take its power.
You saved the ship... again. Thanks, killer.
Hey, hey, hey, that was all me! I mean, no need to thank me, yo, but—yeah, it was all me. I'm gonna stick around. This ship is tight!
So Sanctuary has a voice now. Sure, why not? I can roll with it. Oh, I heard from Clay. He's got a lead on the next fragment. Go meet up with him.
Hey, I can get that open. Navigated, bitches!
Yeah, back in my whip! Don't look like it now, but this thing used to be one fine-ass vessel. Shame I had to crash it.
Yeah, the Family Jewel's seen better days. I'm thinking she ain't flyin' again.

I'm drunk, and I'm scared, boy. Those zealots are after the Vaults, and they'll come for ours. Only a matter of time. So listen. The Grand Reserve, the Oily Graveyard, and the Family Jewel—that's where you'll find the Key. Boy, the Jakobs tree has stood for centuries. Don't let it fall now.
Ah, crap.
Yeah! Let's do this!
Goodbye, GenIVIV! You sucked, and I hated you.
Now come pick me up!
There's so many of them! And they're so goddamn horny!
Okay, what's this? Check—I don't know, don't wanna hit the wrong button... Okay... No, that's a bomb. Okay—maybe this... hm, what'd I do?
She's activated the implosion drive!
Ah, crap! We're in an asteroid field!
Uhh... okay, uh, let's improvise. Hot wiring, that's a thing, right? Grab those wires.
Hey, it's what I do.
Yes. Tell your friends.
Hahahaha... Yes.
Walloping! Love that word. Gonna use that. “Walloping.”
